        <p><strong>2. The Detached Creator:</strong> Though He is the <em>kartāram</em> (creator), Krishna remains <em>akartāram</em> (non-doer). He sets laws in motion but is not "bound" by them. This is the model for perfect leadership: maintaining order while remaining internally free from the ego of being the "doer."</p>
